01/04/2010
CHISINAU, Moldova -- Romania began issuing special travel documents Wednesday (March 31st) to Moldovans living along its eastern border, allowing them to spend up to 90 days on it the country without applying for visas.
Applications for the so-called "small-traffic permits" began March 1st.
According to the Romanian Embassy in Moldova, over 2,500 applications have been received so far.
(Radio Free Europe, Hotnews.ro, Moldnews - 31/03/10)
